@villebro I have made the changes as per your review and all tests have passed. One final question:

It looks like I still need to manually add ``import sqlalchemy_dremio`` in ``dremio.py`` in my local test. How does superset automatically import the one in ``extras_require={``? If not I get the following error when I test the connectivity when adding a new database:

```ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'sqlalchemy_dremio.pyodbc.DremioDialect_pyodbc';'sqlalchemy_dremio.pyodbc' is not a package```

@graceguo-supercat I tested with the following table and data in our Presto (Hive) cluster, and was unable to replicate the error.

```
CREATE TABLE default.superset_test (
  id bigint,
  name varchar,
  list_ints array(bigint),
  list_maps array(map(varchar, varchar)),
  map1 map(varchar, varchar),
  map2 map(varchar, boolean),
  ds date
);

INSERT INTO default.superset_test VALUES (1, 'San Francisco', ARRAY[1,2,3], ARRAY[MAP(ARRAY['foo'], ARRAY['bar']), MAP(ARRAY['fad'], ARRAY['baz'])], MAP(ARRAY['foo'], ARRAY['bar']), MAP(ARRAY['foo'], ARRAY[True]), date '2019-01-09');

select * from default.superset_test;
```

